The platitudes regarding the first point generally take the form of claiming that this is apparently nothing new. True enough, we have had increasing automation in one form or another for centuries. The essential argument is that relieving humans of the mundane work, leaves them free to be more creative and find more interesting things to do. Eventually, this widening of horizons leads to both further technological advances and new jobs in these new fields. One day, technology advances to the point where these jobs themselves become automated, people go off and do something else again, and the process repeats forever ...